verbose_text: Interestingly, H 2 O 2 at 10 M did not decrease the cell viability, however, the level of miR-20b was downregulated, suggesting that the miR-20b expression change was more sensitive to H 2 O 2 stimulation than cell viability change and that the reduced expression in miR-20b at 10 M H 2 O 2 stimulation was not enough to cause decreased cell viability.
